---
import '../styles/global.css';
import PageNav from '../components/PageNav.astro';
import ScenarioLegend from '../components/ScenarioLegend.astro';
import TripleDumbbell from '../components/TripleDumbbell.astro';
import WinnersLosers from '../components/WinnersLosers.astro';
import PercentGain from '../components/PercentGain.astro';
import ScenarioSlope from '../components/ScenarioSlope.astro';
import ScenarioStacks from '../components/ScenarioStacks.astro';
import SmallMultiples from '../components/SmallMultiples.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..144,400;0,9..144,500;0,9..144,600;0,9..144,700;0,9..144,800;0,9..144,900;1,9..144,400;1,9..144,600&family=Jost:wght@300;400;500;600&family=Tiro+Devanagari+Hindi:ital@0;1&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
    <title>Three Parliaments · तीन संसदें · The Indian Census, Part III</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="grain" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="page">

      <PageNav current={3} />

      <hr class="rule double" />

      <header class="masthead">
        <div class="masthead-copy">
          <p class="kicker">Part the Third · Vol. III</p>
          <h1 class="title">
            <span class="title-en">Three</span>
            <span class="title-en-b">Parliaments</span>
            <span class="title-hi">तीन&nbsp;संसदें</span>
          </h1>
          <p class="lede">
            Three Parliaments sit on the page. One exists; two are
            arithmetic. The exercise that follows is not prediction but
            <em>construction</em> — what the House looks like when we apply
            two different rules to the same 2011 population, state by state.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="masthead-figure" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="glyph">¶</div>
          <div class="figure-no">No.<br /><b>III</b></div>
        </div>
      </header>

      <hr class="rule" />

      <ScenarioLegend />

      <hr class="rule" />

      <!-- Cross-reference back to Page 1 Fig. 4 (no duplicate chart) -->
      <aside class="fig-backref">
        <span class="smallcaps">§ the grievance, in one number</span>
        <p>
          Before redrawing, the present. <b>Uttar Pradesh</b> holds
          <b>16.5%</b> of India's population but only <b>14.7%</b> of
          the Lok Sabha — a <em>1.77-percentage-point</em> deficit. The
          twelve small states and UTs, taken together, sit a matching
          distance above their population share. The Freeze Penalty chart
          in <a href="/#freeze-penalty-chart">Fig.&nbsp;4 of the Present</a>
          shows every state's distance from its own numbers.
        </p>
      </aside>

      <hr class="rule" />

      <TripleDumbbell />

      <hr class="rule" />

      <WinnersLosers />

      <hr class="rule" />

      <PercentGain />

      <hr class="rule" />

      <ScenarioSlope />

      <hr class="rule" />

      <ScenarioStacks />

      <hr class="rule double" />

      <section class="chapter-opener">
        <span class="smallcaps">§ the state-level substrate</span>
        <h2 class="chapter-title">
          <span class="chapter-numeral">iv.</span>
          The eighteen that move the map
          <span class="chapter-hi hi">अठारह बड़े राज्य</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="chapter-lede">
          Why the scenarios land the way they do: eighteen state trajectories,
          indexed to their 1901 population. Divergence in the trajectories
          is the mechanism behind divergence in the scenarios.
        </p>
      </section>

      <hr class="rule" />

      <SmallMultiples />

      <hr class="rule double" />

      <aside class="bridge-callout">
        <p>
          The arithmetic is honest.<br />
          <em>Whether it is just is a separate question.</em>
        </p>
      </aside>

      <hr class="rule double" />

      <aside class="next-step">
        <span class="smallcaps">continue reading</span>
        <a href="/editorial/" class="next-link">
          <span class="next-arrow">→</span>
          <span class="next-title">The Consequence</span>
          <span class="next-subtitle hi">परिणाम</span>
        </a>
        <p class="next-blurb">
          The numbers are settled. The politics are not. A case against
          the arithmetic just made.
        </p>
      </aside>

      <hr class="rule" />

      <footer class="colophon">
        <div class="colophon-col">
          <span class="smallcaps">§ method</span>
          <p>
            <b>Scenario&nbsp;1</b> applies <em>⌈seats&thinsp;×&thinsp;1.5⌉</em> to every
            state's current seat count. <b>Scenario&nbsp;2</b> applies
            <em>⌈pop&thinsp;÷&thinsp;14,24,535⌉</em>, using 2011 Census
            populations. Both round up; both enforce a one-seat floor for
            every state and UT; both reproduce the existing seat floor for
            Union Territories currently at one seat.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="colophon-col">
          <span class="smallcaps">§ caveats</span>
          <p>
            These are illustrative redistributions, not forecasts. Actual
            delimitation after 2026 will also account for SC/ST reservation
            under Articles 330–332, within-state boundary re-drawing, and
            the decade's fresh census — none of which is modelled here.
            The magnitudes are the point, not the last decimal.
          </p>
        </div>
      </footer>

      <div class="running-foot">
        <span class="eyebrow">Set in Fraunces &amp; Tiro Devanagari Hindi</span>
        <span class="eyebrow dot">◇</span>
        <span class="eyebrow">Composed on cream</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <script>
      import ApexCharts from 'apexcharts';
      import { REGION_COLORS, REGION_LABELS, REGION_ORDER, type Region } from '../data/census';
      import {
        LOKSABHA_DATA,
        byRegion,
        scenarioGainPct,
      } from '../data/loksabha';

      /* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
         Fig. 6 — Winners & losers (absolute delta, Scenario 2)
         ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
      const winnersSorted = [...LOKSABHA_DATA]
        .filter((r) => r.scenario2Delta !== 0)
        .sort((a, b) => b.scenario2Delta - a.scenario2Delta);
      const winnersColors = winnersSorted.map((r) => REGION_COLORS[r.region]);

      const winnersChart = new ApexCharts(document.querySelector('#winners-chart')!, {
        chart: {
          type: 'bar',
          height: 560,
          fontFamily: '"Jost", "Tiro Devanagari Hindi", system-ui, sans-serif',
          toolbar: { show: false },
          background: 'transparent',
          parentHeightOffset: 0,
        },
        colors: winnersColors,
        series: [{
          name: 'Δ seats',
          data: winnersSorted.map((r) => ({ x: r.name, y: r.scenario2Delta })),
        }],
        plotOptions: {
          bar: {
            horizontal: true,
            barHeight: '70%',
            borderRadius: 0,
            distributed: true,
            dataLabels: { position: 'top' },
          },
        },
        stroke: { show: true, width: 0.5, colors: ['#1a1510'] },
        dataLabels: {
          enabled: true,
          formatter: (v: number) => (v > 0 ? `+${v}` : v < 0 ? `${v}` : ''),
          offsetX: 18,
          style: { fontSize: '11px', fontFamily: '"Fraunces",serif', fontWeight: 700, colors: ['#1a1510'] },
        },
        xaxis: {
          max: 70,
          labels: {
            formatter: (v: string) => {
              const n = Number(v);
              return n > 0 ? `+${n}` : `${n}`;
            },
            style: { fontSize: '11px', fontFamily: '"Jost",sans-serif', colors: '#6b5d4f' },
          },
          axisBorder: { show: true, color: '#1a1510' },
          axisTicks: { show: false },
        },
        yaxis: {
          labels: {
            style: { fontSize: '10.5px', fontFamily: '"Jost",sans-serif', colors: '#1a1510' },
          },
        },
        legend: { show: false },
        grid: {
          borderColor: '#d8cdb8',
          strokeDashArray: 2,
          xaxis: { lines: { show: true } },
          yaxis: { lines: { show: false } },
          padding: { top: 0, right: 60, bottom: 0, left: 8 },
        },
        annotations: {
          xaxis: [
            {
              x: 0,
              borderColor: '#1a1510',
              strokeDashArray: 0,
              borderWidth: 1.5,
            },
          ],
        },
        tooltip: {
          custom: ({ dataPointIndex }: any) => {
            const r = winnersSorted[dataPointIndex];
            const color = REGION_COLORS[r.region];
            const sign = r.scenario2Delta > 0 ? '+' : r.scenario2Delta < 0 ? '' : '±';
            return `<div style="padding:12px 14px;min-width:220px;background:#f5efe3;border:1px solid #1a1510;box-shadow:4px 4px 0 0 #1a1510;font-family:'Jost',sans-serif;color:#1a1510">
              <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;align-items:center;margin-bottom:4px">
                <span style="width:10px;height:10px;background:${color};border:1px solid #1a1510;display:inline-block"></span>
                <span style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-weight:700;font-size:15px">${r.name}</span>
              </div>
              <div style="font-size:10.5px;color:#6b5d4f;margin-bottom:8px;letter-spacing:0.02em">Current: ${r.currentSeats} · Scenario 2: ${r.scenario2Seats}</div>
              <div style="border-top:1px solid #1a1510;padding-top:8px">
                <div style="font-size:10px;color:#6b5d4f;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.14em">delta</div>
                <b style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:26px;color:${r.scenario2Delta > 0 ? '#8c2e1a' : r.scenario2Delta < 0 ? '#1f4d54' : '#6b5d4f'}">${sign}${r.scenario2Delta}</b>
              </div>
            </div>`;
          },
        },
      });
      winnersChart.render();

      /* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
         Fig. 7 — Percentage gain (Scenario 2 relative to current)
         ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
      const pctRows = [...LOKSABHA_DATA]
        .filter((r) => r.scenario2Delta !== 0)
        .map((r) => ({ ...r, pct: scenarioGainPct(r, 2) }))
        .sort((a, b) => b.pct - a.pct);
      const pctColors = pctRows.map((r) => REGION_COLORS[r.region]);

      const pctChart = new ApexCharts(document.querySelector('#pct-gain-chart')!, {
        chart: {
          type: 'bar',
          height: 560,
          fontFamily: '"Jost", "Tiro Devanagari Hindi", system-ui, sans-serif',
          toolbar: { show: false },
          background: 'transparent',
          parentHeightOffset: 0,
        },
        colors: pctColors,
        series: [{
          name: '% change',
          data: pctRows.map((r) => ({ x: r.name, y: +r.pct.toFixed(1) })),
        }],
        plotOptions: {
          bar: {
            horizontal: true,
            barHeight: '70%',
            borderRadius: 0,
            distributed: true,
            dataLabels: { position: 'top' },
          },
        },
        stroke: { show: true, width: 0.5, colors: ['#1a1510'] },
        dataLabels: {
          enabled: true,
          formatter: (v: number) => (v > 0 ? `+${v.toFixed(0)}%` : v < 0 ? `${v.toFixed(0)}%` : ''),
          offsetX: 22,
          style: { fontSize: '11px', fontFamily: '"Fraunces",serif', fontWeight: 700, colors: ['#1a1510'] },
        },
        xaxis: {
          max: 100,
          labels: {
            formatter: (v: string) => `${Number(v).toFixed(0)}%`,
            style: { fontSize: '11px', fontFamily: '"Jost",sans-serif', colors: '#6b5d4f' },
          },
          axisBorder: { show: true, color: '#1a1510' },
          axisTicks: { show: false },
        },
        yaxis: {
          labels: {
            style: { fontSize: '10.5px', fontFamily: '"Jost",sans-serif', colors: '#1a1510' },
          },
        },
        legend: { show: false },
        grid: {
          borderColor: '#d8cdb8',
          strokeDashArray: 2,
          xaxis: { lines: { show: true } },
          yaxis: { lines: { show: false } },
          padding: { top: 0, right: 60, bottom: 0, left: 8 },
        },
        annotations: {
          xaxis: [
            { x: 0, borderColor: '#1a1510', strokeDashArray: 0, borderWidth: 1.5 },
            {
              x: 50,
              borderColor: '#8c2e1a',
              strokeDashArray: 4,
              borderWidth: 1,
              label: {
                text: '+50% · the Scenario 1 baseline',
                orientation: 'horizontal',
                position: 'top',
                offsetY: -6,
                borderWidth: 0,
                style: {
                  color: '#8c2e1a',
                  background: '#f5efe3',
                  fontFamily: '"Fraunces",serif',
                  fontSize: '11px',
                  fontWeight: 600,
                  padding: { left: 6, right: 6, top: 2, bottom: 2 },
                },
              },
            },
          ],
        },
        tooltip: {
          custom: ({ dataPointIndex }: any) => {
            const r = pctRows[dataPointIndex];
            const color = REGION_COLORS[r.region];
            return `<div style="padding:12px 14px;min-width:220px;background:#f5efe3;border:1px solid #1a1510;box-shadow:4px 4px 0 0 #1a1510;font-family:'Jost',sans-serif;color:#1a1510">
              <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;align-items:center;margin-bottom:4px">
                <span style="width:10px;height:10px;background:${color};border:1px solid #1a1510;display:inline-block"></span>
                <span style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-weight:700;font-size:15px">${r.name}</span>
              </div>
              <div style="font-size:10.5px;color:#6b5d4f;margin-bottom:8px;letter-spacing:0.02em">${r.currentSeats} → ${r.scenario2Seats} seats &nbsp;(+${r.scenario2Delta})</div>
              <div style="border-top:1px solid #1a1510;padding-top:8px">
                <div style="font-size:10px;color:#6b5d4f;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.14em">relative change</div>
                <b style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:26px;color:#8c2e1a">+${r.pct.toFixed(1)}%</b>
              </div>
            </div>`;
          },
        },
      });
      pctChart.render();

      /* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
         Fig. 9 — Regional reshuffle (three-scenario stacked bars)
         ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
      const curByRegion = byRegion('currentSeats');
      const s1ByRegion = byRegion('scenario1Seats');
      const s2ByRegion = byRegion('scenario2Seats');
      const stackedSeries = REGION_ORDER.map((r) => ({
        name: REGION_LABELS[r].en,
        data: [curByRegion[r], s1ByRegion[r], s2ByRegion[r]],
      }));

      const stacksChart = new ApexCharts(document.querySelector('#stacks-chart')!, {
        chart: {
          type: 'bar',
          stacked: true,
          stackType: '100%',
          height: 420,
          fontFamily: '"Jost", "Tiro Devanagari Hindi", system-ui, sans-serif',
          toolbar: { show: false },
          background: 'transparent',
          parentHeightOffset: 0,
        },
        colors: REGION_ORDER.map((r) => REGION_COLORS[r]),
        series: stackedSeries,
        plotOptions: {
          bar: {
            horizontal: false,
            columnWidth: '50%',
            borderRadius: 0,
            dataLabels: { position: 'center' },
          },
        },
        stroke: { show: true, width: 1, colors: ['#1a1510'] },
        dataLabels: {
          enabled: true,
          formatter: (v: number) => (v >= 6 ? `${Math.round(v)}%` : ''),
          style: { fontSize: '12px', fontFamily: '"Fraunces",serif', fontWeight: 700, colors: ['#f5efe3'] },
        },
        xaxis: {
          categories: ['Current', 'Scenario 1', 'Scenario 2'],
          labels: {
            style: { fontSize: '11px', fontFamily: '"Jost",sans-serif', colors: '#1a1510', fontWeight: 500 },
          },
          axisBorder: { show: true, color: '#1a1510' },
          axisTicks: { show: false },
        },
        yaxis: {
          labels: {
            formatter: (v: number) => `${v.toFixed(0)}%`,
            style: { fontSize: '11px', fontFamily: '"Jost",sans-serif', colors: '#6b5d4f' },
          },
        },
        legend: {
          position: 'top',
          horizontalAlign: 'left',
          fontFamily: '"Jost",sans-serif',
          fontSize: '12px',
          labels: { colors: '#1a1510' },
          markers: { size: 8, strokeWidth: 1, shape: 'square' },
          itemMargin: { horizontal: 14, vertical: 4 },
          offsetY: -4,
        },
        grid: {
          borderColor: '#d8cdb8',
          strokeDashArray: 2,
          padding: { top: 6, right: 12, bottom: 0, left: 8 },
        },
        tooltip: { enabled: false },
      });
      stacksChart.render();

      /* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
         Small multiples — each of the Big Eighteen states' population
         trajectory 1901 → 2011 (indexed to 1901 = 100).
         This component renders its own SVG in frontmatter; no JS needed.
         ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

      // Staggered entrance — trigger after first paint
      requestAnimationFrame(() => {
        document.body.classList.add('ready');
      });
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
